		<hr/>
		<p>Kaela opened the door with her three-year-old brother on her hip, happily surprised to see Joey. "Hey, stranger," she grinned, "haven't seen you in hours. Dominick, this is my friend Joey. Do you want to say hi?" The child buried his head against his sister's chest in response, his legs gripping her tightly. "It's okay," she whispered to Joey, "he just takes a little while with new people."</p>
		<p>Joey couldn't help noticing that Dominick was much darker than Kaela-- actually, he was black. Could it be that Bessie and Bodie weren't the only interracial couple in Capeside after all?</p>
