		<p>Not for food, anyway, she thought to herself, devilishly recalling her recent exploits. They went down the hall to Kaela's room, and the sweet, musty smell of incense hit Joey as soon as she opened the door. The room looked just like the incense smelled, Joey thought-- sweet and mysterious, a bit otherworldly. A richly embroidered tapestry hung over the window, and the walls were painted a cool, minty green color, with dark green borders.</p>
